Meta-Role

One pattern I notice across the Money Bin is that most daemons already fall into three broad categories:

* Sensors — observe reality (Spy, Semantic LiDAR, Tracer Dye, Blink)
* Processors — interpret and transform (Spider, Checksum, Architect, Prism, Comparative Distillation)
* Actuators — change the world or the system (Raven, Farmer, Herding Dog, Goblin, Gardener)

The Spy fits naturally as a sensor that improves the quality of information entering the entire system. It doesn’t replace any existing daemon; it raises the effectiveness of all of them by helping ensure they begin with better observations, better context, and clearer uncertainty estimates. That role also complements one of your recurring themes: preserving a disciplined loop where observation precedes interpretation, and interpretation precedes action.